// CONDITIONAL EXPRESSION
these are used to write the many lines of code in one line

1. SYNTAX:
condition ? exp1 : exp2;

// if the cndtn is true it evalutes the exp1 and return its value 
// if the cndtn is false it evalutes the exp2 and return its value 


void main(){
  int a = 2;
  int b = 3;
  a < b ? print('$a is smaller'): print('$b is smaller');
}
output:
2 is smaller

